{{Infobox power station | name = Fuqing Nuclear Power Plant | name_official = 福清核电站 | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = China | location_map_size = | location_map_caption= | location_map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|25|26|45|N|119|26|50|E|region:CN-35_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = China | location = Qianxue, [[Fuqing]], [[Fujian]] | status = O | construction_began = 21 November 2008 | commissioned = 22 November 2014 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = Fujian Fuqing Nuclear Co. | operator = [[China National Nuclear Corporation]] (CNNC) | np_reactor_type = PWR | ps_units_operational= 4 × 1089&nbsp;MW | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_units_uc = 2 × 1150&nbsp;MW | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_electrical_capacity= 4356 | ps_electrical_cap_fac= | ps_annual_generation= | th_cogeneration = | th_combined_cycle = | website = | extra = }} The '''Fuqing Nuclear Power Plant''' ({{zh|s=福清核电站|t=福清核電站|p=Fúqīng Hédiànzhàn}}) is a [[nuclear power plant]] in [[Fuqing]], [[Fujian Province]], [[China]]. The plant is located on the coast of [[Xinghua Bay]], near Qianxue Village, [[Sanshan, Fuqing|Sanshan Town]].<ref name="pdo">{{cite news | url= http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/90001/90776/90881/6539547.html | title= Construction of Fuqing Nuclear Power Plant commences | date= 24 November 2008 | work= [[People's Daily]] Online |publisher= | accessdate= 2009-11-13 }}</ref> The station has four 1,089&nbsp;[[megawatt]] (MW) [[CPR-1000]] [[pressurized water reactor]]s (PWRs).<ref name="wna-China">{{cite web | url= http://www.world-nuclear.org/information-library/country-profiles/countries-a-f/china-nuclear-power.aspx | title= Nuclear Power in China | date= October 2016 | work= Country Briefings | publisher= [[World Nuclear Association]] (WNA) | accessdate= 25 October 2016 }}</ref> The CPR-1000 is an advanced PWR design developed by China from the [[Areva]]-designed PWRs at the [[Daya Bay Nuclear Power Plant]].<ref name="wnn-23706">{{cite news | url= http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/newsarticle.aspx?id=23706 | title= Construction gets under way at Chinese sites | date= 24 November 2008 | work= [[World Nuclear News]] | publisher= WNA | accessdate= 2009-11-13 }}</ref> The plant was jointly constructed and is operated by [[China National Nuclear Corporation]] (51%), China Huadian Corp. (39%) and the Fujian Investment & Development Co Ltd. (10%).
Construction of the first unit began on 21&nbsp;November 2008<ref name="wna-China"/> and was completed in 2014. First concrete for Unit&nbsp;2 was poured on 17&nbsp;June 2009<ref name="wnn-25474"/> and the unit was started in October 2015. First concrete for Unit&nbsp;3 was poured on 31&nbsp;December 2010. Construction of Unit&nbsp;4 was to begin in 2011, but was delayed until November 2012 by China's nuclear safety review after the Japanese nuclear accident.
In November 2014 it was announced that units 5 and 6 would be of the [[Hualong One]] (updated CPR-1000) design, with unit 5 scheduled to be in operation about 2019.<ref name=wnn-20141104>{{cite news |url=http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-Hualong-One-deployment-at-Fuqing-5-0411141.html |title=Hualong One deployment at Fuqing 5 |publisher=World Nuclear News |date=4 November 2014 |accessdate=9 March 2015}}</ref> The first concrete was poured for Fuqing 5 on 7 May 2015.<ref name=wnn-0705154>{{cite news | url= http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-China-starts-building-first-Hualong-One-unit-0705154.html | title= China starts building first Hualong One unit |date= 7 May 2015 |work= World Nuclear News |publisher= | accessdate= 7 May 2015 }}</ref>
