'''True muonium''' or '''muononium''' is a theoretically predicted [[exotic atom]] made up of an [[Muon|antimuon]] and a [[muon]]. It is yet to be observed, but it may have been generated in the collision of electron and positron beams.<ref>{{cite journal |author=S.J. Brodsky, R.F. Lebed |year=2009 |title=Production of the smallest QED atom: True muonium (''µ''⁺''µ''⁻) |journal=[[Physical Review Letters]] |volume=102 |issue=21 |pages=213401 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.102.213401|pmid=19519103 |bibcode=2009PhRvL.102u3401B|arxiv = 0904.2225 }}</ref><ref>{{cite arXiv |author=H. Lamm, R.F. Lebed |year=2013 |title=True Muonium (µ⁺µ⁻) on the Light Front: A Toy Model|eprint = 1311.3245|class=hep-ph }}</ref>
