{{Infobox power station | name = Tunø Knob | name_official = Tunø Knob Offshore Wind Farm | image = File:Tunø Knob Vindmøllepark 01.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = Tunø Knob Offshore Wind Farm | image_alt = | location_map = Denmark | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|55|58|10|N|10|21|20|E|type:landmark_region:DK|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = [[Denmark]] | location = [[Odder Municipality]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = {{Start date|1995}} | decommissioned = | cost = [[Pound sterling|£]]10m | owner = [[DONG Energy]] | operator = | ps_units_manu_model = [[Vestas]] V39 500kW | wind_hub_height = | wind_rotor_diameter = | wind_rated_speed = | wind_farm_type = | wind_site_area = | wind_offshore_depth = {{cvt|7|m|ft|0}} | wind_offshore_distance = {{cvt|6|km|0}} | ps_units_operational = 10 x 500&nbsp;kW | ps_electrical_capacity = 5 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = 29.7% | website = {{URL|http://www.mhivestasoffshore.com/tunoe-knob/|Tunoe Knob}} | extra = }}
'''Tunø Knob Offshore Wind Farm''' is an [[offshore wind power|offshore]] [[wind farm]] in the [[Bay of Aarhus]], Denmark. It is located on the sandbar Tunø Knob, west of the [[Tunø]] island.
The wind farm was commissioned in 1995 with 10 turbines, each a 500&nbsp;kW [[Vestas]] V39.<ref name="ensStats">Spliid, Iben B. [http://www.ens.dk/sites/ens.dk/files/byggeri/anlaegprodtilnettet.xls Data on operating and decommissioned wind turbines (as at end of September 2010)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140802232057/http://www.ens.dk/sites/ens.dk/files/byggeri/anlaegprodtilnettet.xls |date=2014-08-02 }} (.xls spreadsheet) ''[[Danish Energy Agency]]'', 18 October 2010. [http://www.ens.dk/en-US/Info/FactsAndFigures/Energy_statistics_and_indicators/OverviewOfTheEnergySector/RegisterOfWindTurbines/Sider/Forside.aspx Main page] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130415092033/http://www.ens.dk/en-US/Info/FactsAndFigures/Energy_statistics_and_indicators/OverviewOfTheEnergySector/RegisterOfWindTurbines/Sider/Forside.aspx |date=2013-04-15 }} Retrieved: 25 October 2010.</ref><!--ENS ID 570715000000023972--><ref name="eweatable09">[http://www.ewea.org/fileadmin/ewea_documents/documents/statistics/OperationalOffshoreFarms2009.pdf Operational offshore wind farms in Europe, end 2009] ''[[EWEA]]''. Retrieved: 23 October 2010.</ref><ref name="osstudy">Christensen, Allan S. & Madsen, Morten. [http://www.offshore-power.net/Files/Filer/danish_supply_chain_study.pdf Supply Chain study on the Danish offshore wind industry] {{Webarchive|url=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20160515045800/http://www.offshore-power.net/Files/Filer/danish_supply_chain_study.pdf |date=2016-05-15 }} page 33-42 ''Offshore Center Denmark'', 29. august 2005. Retrieved: 23 October 2010.</ref><ref>[http://www.offshorewindenergy.org/windfarms/display_data_windfarm.php?id=18 Tunø Offshore wind energy listing] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727141449/http://www.offshorewindenergy.org/windfarms/display_data_windfarm.php?id=18 |date=2011-07-27 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.4coffshore.com/windfarms/tuno-knob-denmark-dk05.html 4cOffshore listing for Tunø Knob]</ref> The turbines are 45 metres high, based on concrete foundations at 3-6 meter deep waters, and together they produce enough electricity to supply c. 2,800 households.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arkark.dk/building.aspx?buildingid=1700|title=Tunø Knob vindmøllepark, Odder|publisher=ArkArk.dk|date=|language=Danish|accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref> The Tunø Knob Offshore Wind Farm was the first offshore wind farm by Danish wind turbine company Vestas.
